  <h1>AI Judge Report</h1>
  <p><strong>Baseline exam:</strong> AP CS A (#265)<br/>
     <strong>Variant exam:</strong> AP CS A — Exam A (#266)<br/>
     <strong>Model:</strong> ollama:gpt-oss:120b<br/>
     <strong>Compared slots:</strong> 47</p>

  <h2>Overall score</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>Final exam variant score: <strong>85</strong> / 100<br/>
       Base (rubric-only): <strong>94</strong> / 100<br/>
       Usable questions: <strong>100</strong>%<br/>
       Distinctness: <strong>4.26</strong>/5 (factor 0.92)</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Instructor summary</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p><strong>Summary:</strong> The variant closely mirrors the baseline in concept, difficulty, structure, and answer quality, yielding a high overall score and strong usability. Minor refinements could boost distinctness and polish distractors.</p>
    <p><strong>Strengths:</strong> High conceptual equivalence, Very similar difficulty level, Clear and solvable structure, Accurate answer key with plausible distractors</p>
    <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong> Distinctness could be increased with more varied numbers or context, Slight inconsistencies in distractor plausibility, Minor wording tweaks could improve clarity</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Aggregate scores</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>Conceptual equivalence: <strong>4.83</strong><br/>
       Difficulty similarity: <strong>4.51</strong><br/>
       Structural validity: <strong>4.91</strong><br/>
       Answer correctness: <strong>4.49</strong><br/>
       Topic alignment: <strong>4.96</strong></p>
  </div>

  <h2>Usability</h2>
